This paper deals with social choice functions, which are commonly studied in the field of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of randomized algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.AI) and learning theory (cs.LG). The study of participation incentives is related to game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses specific types of preferences, such as downward lexicographic and stochastic dominance, which are relevant to mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
